description:
&lt;p&gt;The East &amp; North Herts NHS Trust are looking to recruit an Audiologist. We offer a wide range of services across 3 Hospital Sites in Stevenage, Welwyn Garden City &amp; Hertford and satellite sites including:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- Full diagnostic support and rehabilitation services to 6 ENT consultants&lt;br /&gt;- Direct Access Hearing Aid Clinics.&lt;br /&gt;- Balance Assessment Clinics using Caloric &amp; ENG / VNG testing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Auditory Middle Ear implants &lt;br /&gt;- Tinnitus clinics.&lt;br /&gt;- Dedicated paediatric clinics including VRA / ABR/ Steady State / OAE.&lt;br /&gt;- NHSP.&lt;br /&gt;- Research / Auditing.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The department provides a comprehensive diagnostic and rehabilitative service to the population of East &amp; North Hertfordshire and surrounding areas. The Audiology department operates a number of services including adult hearing aid service, diagnostic vestibular and children&#39;s assessments. This post will allow applicants to develop their interest in adult rehab and vestibular diagnostics. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Applicants must hold a BSc in Audiology or equivalent qualifications. Applicants should also have, or be able to achieve RCCP registration, and membership of BAA while not essential is desirable.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This post is suitable for newly qualified graduate audiologists.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Giles Whiley - Head of Audiology&lt;br /&gt;gwhiley@nhs.net&lt;br /&gt;01438 284055&lt;/p&gt;
